# AI tooling — restarting work on `chi-to-bow-bridge`

Use this note when switching machines, restarting terminals, or moving between assistants (Cursor, CLI agents, Gemini in terminal, etc.). Update it when tooling or checkpoints change.

## Repo in one sentence

Starter **CHI ↔ BoW** bridge RTL with **Cocotb** (Icarus), optional **Verilator + C++** (`vlate_bench/`), optional **Synopsys VCS + UVM** (`uvm_bench/`). Canonical verification map: **[docs/PLAN.md](docs/PLAN.md)**.

## Sync and baseline

```bash
cd /path/to/chi-to-bow-bridge
git fetch && git status   # preferably on latest main before a long agent run
make doctor && make       # Cocotb + integration + docs (matches CI job `test`)
make -C vlate_bench lint && make -C vlate_bench run   # Verilator (+ CI parity)
```

VCS/UVM is local-only: `make -C uvm_bench run` (see `uvm_bench/README.md`).

## Cursor (IDE Agent / Chat)

1. Open the repo root as the workspace (`File → Open Folder`).
2. In a new composer/chat, paste **Context** plus **Goal** below (edit the Goal line).
3. For repeatable project rules: `.cursor/rules/` or Cursor **Rules for AI** pointing at RTL style and “only change scoped files”.
4. Transcripts persist under your Cursor project dir (not in-repo); rely on **`docs/PLAN.md`** scenario matrix + this file for continuity.

**Context** (paste as needed):

```
Repo: chi-to-bow-bridge — CHI-to-BoW bridge RTL.
Verification matrix + CI policy: docs/PLAN.md
Block Cocotb: test/ ; integration Cocotb: integration/
Verilator TB: vlate_bench/ (make lint ; make run)
UVM TB: uvm_bench/ (Synopsys VCS, not in CI)
```

**Goal**: _fill in_: e.g. “Extend burst write datapath per PLAN RTL milestone #1.”

## Cursor CLI (terminal agent)

Runs outside the IDE; same repo context.

```bash
cd /path/to/chi-to-bow-bridge
# Example (adjust flags to match your install):
cursor-agent . "Task: … ; read docs/PLAN.md and …"
```

If your workflow uses **`AGENTS.md`** or **`CLAUDE.md`**, add a one-line pointer there to `docs/PLAN.md` so headless runs pick up the matrix.

## Google Gemini CLI (terminal)

Resume only works for **the same local session id**; copy a fresh id from tool output when you start a long job.

```bash
# Example pattern (your binary/flags may differ):
gemini --resume <SESSION_ID>
```

Replace `<SESSION_ID>` with the id the CLI printed (old ids in prior scratch notes are not reliable). If resume is unavailable, start a new session and paste the **Context** block from the Cursor section above.

## Other assistants (ChatGPT, web Copilot, etc.)

Paste the **Context** block and attach or paste the relevant sections of `docs/PLAN.md` (matrix + milestone list). Do not assume they see your full tree.

## What to update when you “checkpoint”

After a merge or important local commit, optionally add a line here:

- **Last known good**: `git rev-parse --short HEAD` + date
- **Open risks**: e.g. “UVM not run in CI”

